<p>Armed men raided St. Mary’s School, a Catholic boarding school in the Papiri community of Agwara LGA, Niger State, on Friday, abducting hundreds of students and staff [theglobeandmail.com#1][bbc.com#1]. The Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN) later revised the tally to at least 303 students and 12 teachers after a verification and final headcount, up from initial counts of 215–227 [france24.com#1][japantoday.com#1][bbc.com#1][dw.com#1][japantoday.com#2]. Nigerian police and military forces were deployed to search for the abductees [dw.com#1]. It was the second mass school abduction reported in Nigeria this week [nytimes.com#1][newarab.com#1][theguardian.com#1]. President Trump threatened possible U.S. military action, while the Nigerian government rejected claims of a “Christian genocide” [washingtonpost.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/NYYbYNtBq5AtkRMeqn-rNt4nsQ3T2D4IEw3F-XBfHitWlvqBASZjzBqxwB4jZtf-hvZz-EE6rSKSFTHhprzBXR-y1gypoiZN84ygYMA7kMLF_LFjr8F46GkVmUICJeDGXzR47mRyr2gsvBcVqBRyw5zmyDlBbFs6FA0cLhhQR2fzcQ-0VLztQQEfatI' alt='Police outside a school in Kebbi after a kidnapping earlier in the week; Friday’s attack struck neighboring Niger State.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Updated headcount: CAN said 303 students and 12 teachers were kidnapped after a verification and final headcount, revising earlier figures upward [france24.com#1][japantoday.com#1].</li><li>Where it happened: The attack targeted St. Mary’s School in the Papiri community of Agwara Local Government Area, Niger State [theglobeandmail.com#1].</li><li>Casualty reported: One person was shot during the attack; initial reports said 227 people were abducted, including 12 teachers and 215 children [dw.com#2].</li><li>Security response: Nigerian police and military forces were deployed to search for the missing students and staff [dw.com#1].</li><li>Wider context: This is the second mass school abduction reported in Nigeria this week [nytimes.com#1][newarab.com#1][theguardian.com#1][dw.com#1].</li><li>International pressure: President Trump threatened potential U.S. military action; the Nigerian government rejects claims of a “Christian genocide” [washingtonpost.com#1][theguardian.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN): Revised the number of abductees to 303 students and 12 teachers after verification and a final headcount [france24.com#1][japantoday.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251122-attacks-in-nigeria-over-300-students-and-staff-kidnapped-in-niger-state-raid'>FRANCE 24; Japan Today</a>)</li><li>Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN): Confirmed the Catholic boarding school was targeted and that both pupils and teachers were taken [theglobeandmail.com#1][bbc.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/article-gunmen-abduction-nigeria-catholic-school/'>The Globe and Mail; BBC</a>)</li><li>Nigerian security forces: Police and military units were deployed to search for the missing students and staff [dw.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dw.com/en/nigeria-over-200-students-abducted-from-catholic-school/a-74831286'>DW</a>)</li><li>United States (President Trump): Threatened possible military force as Washington pressures Abuja to protect Christian communities [washingtonpost.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2025/11/22/nigeria-school-kidnapping-christians-trump/'>Washington Post</a>)</li><li>Nigerian government: Denied that a “Christian genocide” is occurring amid heightened rhetoric [theguardian.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/2025/nov/21/nigeria-reels-after-second-mass-school-abduction-in-a-week'>The Guardian</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1p39en0/gunmen_abduct_more_than_200_schoolchildren_and_12/'>Gunmen abduct more than 200 schoolchildren and 12 teachers in attack on Nigerian Catholic school</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytime